USX Corp's USS division said itit intends to close its Geneva Works near Provo, Utah,effective July one.    The company said it is continuing talks with localinterests in Utah concerning a possible sale of the Genevaworks plant.    The company had announced the indefinite idling of theintegrated steel mill in February. The plant, which producedflat rolled steel products and small diameter pipe, hademployeed 2,200 workers, the company said. Reuter&#3;